    <item>
      <title>Re: Thoughts of a... resting... EQ player</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=78148#M78148</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Here is my suggestion for death penalty.&amp;nbsp; Reduce exp penalty by 75%.&amp;nbsp; Change the 96% Cleric rez to a Cleric 84% rez.&amp;nbsp; This will have the exact same effect as a 96% rez with current death penalty.&amp;nbsp; All other rez spells should be adjusted to provide some bonus over the default 75%, but less than the best cleric rez.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The result of this system is that for groups that have a cleric, there is no change.&amp;nbsp; For groups with a weaker or no-rezzer, they will see significant less exp loss from the new system.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;One other thing to consider.&amp;nbsp; Death penalty sub 40 really isn't that severe even if you don't get a rez.&amp;nbsp; It is post 40 where the amount of time that you lose in a death really starts to scale.&amp;nbsp; The ideal rez system is one that would penalize early levels more and higher levels less since it takes the higher level more time to pay off the lost experience.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;KEI and Virtue are two "must have" buffs for higher level content.&amp;nbsp; I think the current pok supply isn't too bad (although it is harder to find KEI casters these days), however it would be an option to reduce mana bonus effects, and increase innate mana regen, so that the absence of a particular buff would not be that punishing to a player.&amp;nbsp; Same thing could be done with virtue, but that would have other balance issues to consider since silk classes get a significant portion of their hp from the buff, more so than a tank class.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
